Key Match Events: Seth Lugo struck out 10 in seven masterful innings and Salvador Perez hit two run-scoring singles to reach 100 RBIs for the second time
Miscellaneous Highlights: Tommy Pham homered and Bobby Witt Jr. had an RBI single
Others: Seth Lugo tied Atlanta ace Chris Sale and Detroit lefty Tarik Skubal for most wins in the majors
Kris Bubic and John Schreiber each fanned two in a perfect inning to complete the three-hitter, as New York failed to advance a runner to second base
